{"id":3106,"date":"2022-11-01T12:39:27","date_gmt":"2022-11-01T12:39:27","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/?page_id=3106"},"modified":"2023-04-09T18:59:15","modified_gmt":"2023-04-09T18:59:15","slug":"home","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/","title":{"rendered":""},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\"><span style=\"color: #ff3333;\">The Zip Code Memory Project<\/span> seeks to find community-based ways to memorialize the devastating losses resulting from the Coronavirus pandemic while also acknowledging its radically differential effects on Upper New York City neighborhoods. Through a series of art-based workshops, public events, social media platforms, and a performance\/exhibition at the Cathedral of St John the Divine, community members re-imagine Zip Codes not as zones of separation, but as interrelated spaces for connectivity and mutual care.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2400\" height=\"183\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3316\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4.jpg 2400w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4-300x23.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4-1024x78.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4-768x59.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4-1536x117.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4-2048x156.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zcmpnet4-2000x153.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\">Projects<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-4\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/WORKSHOPShome-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3584\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/WORKSHOPShome-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/WORKSHOPShome-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/WORKSHOPShome-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/WORKSHOPShome-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/WORKSHOPShome.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Workshops<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The ZCMP workshops built on each other to develop trust among a diverse group of participants who had experienced the pandemic in radically different ways. Through acting exercises and games; storytelling, writing and art-making; and through discussions about how we can promote social change, we aimed to work through loss, enable healing, and create community.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/workshops\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-8\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roundtables<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">To reflect on and supplement the work done in our workshops and gatherings, we invited the memorial artists and architects, geographers and demographers, epidemiologists and public health experts we have found inspiring to join us in several public roundtable discussions on Reparative Memory, the determinative power of Zip Codes, and Chronic Lives. Project participants joined for several participatory roundtables to reflect on \u201cCovid Three Years Later.\u201d Roundtables were co-sponsored with our partners.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/roundtables\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"498\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/roundtables-1024x498.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3925\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/roundtables-1024x498.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/roundtables-300x146.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/roundtables-768x374.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/roundtables.jpg 1435w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-12\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/exhibitionhomepage-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3587\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/exhibitionhomepage-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/exhibitionhomepage-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/exhibitionhomepage-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/exhibitionhomepage-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/exhibitionhomepage.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Imagine Repair Exhibition<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The \u201cImagine Repair\u201d exhibition featured work produced in our workshops and specially commissioned for the exhibit. The included artists searched for forms that convey their responsibility to bear witness to an extraordinary historical moment. They came together to celebrate the restorative power of artistic collaboration and community, and to express a collective desire for renewed hope and a demand for transformative justice.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/exhibition\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-16\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Performances &amp; Presentations<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">We invited the general public to listen to presentations and participate in performances. The songs, chants, rants, secular sermons, and clanging of pots created a space in which our outrage and anger could give way to hope and joy in our togetherness. In the Nave of the Cathedral of St. John the Divine, we placed signs marked \u201cPresente!\u201d on multiple chairs to hold a space for those who are no longer here.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/performances-and-exhibitions\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/performanceshomepage-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3588\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/performanceshomepage-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/performanceshomepage-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/performanceshomepage-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/performanceshomepage-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/performanceshomepage.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-20\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/filmhomepage-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3589\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/filmhomepage-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/filmhomepage-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/filmhomepage-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/filmhomepage-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/filmhomepage.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Film<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><em>Together, Not Alone<\/em>, 2022, a short film about the ZCMP directed by Gabriella Canal and Judith Helfand, &nbsp;shows how a group of strangers from across three New York City neighborhoods\u2014different ages, races, socio-economic backgrounds, work and life experience \u2013 come together after months of Covid-19 isolation to explore, map, paint, shape, recall and bear witness to eachothers\u2019 zip code-determined struggles and imagine justice and repair.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/together-not-alone-2\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-24\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Gatherings<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Our gatherings allowed participants and the broader community to participate in a much needed candle-light vigil with testimonials, music, and song. We interacted with each other&#8217;s body maps; our postcards reflected on \u201cWhat have we lost and learned from Covid? How can we heal and grow together?\u201d Our walk through the neighborhood, accompanied by drums and chanting, made the loss and mourning visible, demanding acknowledgment. The Sing Harlem Choir reminded us that there was hope and beauty, even in the dark.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/gatherings\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">Visit<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/gatheringshomepage-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3590\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/gatheringshomepage-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/gatheringshomepage-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/gatheringshomepage-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/gatheringshomepage-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/gatheringshomepage.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2400\" height=\"183\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3359\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1.jpg 2400w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1-300x23.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1-1024x78.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1-768x59.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1-1536x117.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1-2048x156.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/ZCMP_LINE-1-2000x153.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\">Reflections<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-31\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"340\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zipcodes.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3116\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zipcodes.jpeg 512w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/zipcodes-300x199.jpeg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Zip Codes<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Zip Codes, introduced in the 1960s, soon became a shorthand for significant and sometimes brutal social inequalities affecting the lives and life expectancies of different communities. ZCMP mapping taught us new ways to conceptualize how we are and are not the same even as we are governed together.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>10027, that\u2019s Central Harlem\u2026What I love about my community is that there are still pockets where people really look out for each other.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/zip-codes\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/BODIES_211024_GeoWSGrp2_021_DDR-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3614\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/BODIES_211024_GeoWSGrp2_021_DDR-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/BODIES_211024_GeoWSGrp2_021_DDR-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/BODIES_211024_GeoWSGrp2_021_DDR-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/BODIES_211024_GeoWSGrp2_021_DDR-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/BODIES_211024_GeoWSGrp2_021_DDR-2048x1363.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/BODIES_211024_GeoWSGrp2_021_DDR-2000x1331.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bodies<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Individual and social bodies were ravaged by COVID. ZCMP brought people together again in public, to rebuild bodily connections with those they did not know\u2013touching, looking into each other&#8217;s eyes, remembering that we all have names even as we recognized what had been lost.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>My body is in exile.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/bodies\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Memory_22Mar6-SJR-13-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3617\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Memory_22Mar6-SJR-13-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Memory_22Mar6-SJR-13-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Memory_22Mar6-SJR-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Memory_22Mar6-SJR-13-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Memory_22Mar6-SJR-13-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Memory_22Mar6-SJR-13-2000x1333.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Memory<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>How do we memorialize an ongoing crisis that is being publically minimized and disavowed? How can traumatic memory be transformed into activist engagement for social justice?&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>We didn\u2019t get to join together in prayer.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/memory-2\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-38\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"340\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/imagine.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3113\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/imagine.jpeg 512w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/imagine-300x199.jpeg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Imagine<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The ZCMP art-based workshops, performances, and art exhibition offered a safe context in which we could act out and thus transform disabling memories. Together, through acts of mutual care, we can imagine an otherwise.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>The Zip Code Memory project provides a space for us to imagine a future where we are healthy, safe, and happily in community with people who care deeply about the city.&nbsp; After all the isolation and pain caused by the pandemic, meeting in person for the first time allowed me to feel reconnected with the world again.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/imagine-2\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/repair-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3849\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/repair-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/repair-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/repair-768x511.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/repair-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/repair-2048x1363.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/repair-2000x1331.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Repair<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Repair meant assuming responsibility for the dysfunction that exacerbated the effects of&nbsp; the pandemic, and the admission that there is no better before to go back to. ZCMP was conceived as a process of seeing, listening, acknowledging and, where possible, addressing past wrongs and alleviating present pain in creative, even joyful ways.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>You can\u2019t heal what you refuse to see.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/repair-2\/\" style=\"border-radius:1px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"341\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/justice.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3114\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/justice.jpeg 512w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/justice-300x200.jpeg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Justice<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Justice, as a right, as a demand, was an aspiration motivating the ZCMP. How could ZCMP\u2019s practices of collective trust and hope transform our desire for a better future into a demand for accountability and change?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/justice-2\/\" style=\"border-radius:0px\">VISIT<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" id=\"covidanchor\"><strong>How do you know Covid?<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-41\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Intros _ 1.mp4\" src=\"https:\/\/player.vimeo.com\/video\/785042362?h=3fcabdaa65&amp;dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963\" width=\"950\" height=\"534\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Intros _ 2\" src=\"https:\/\/player.vimeo.com\/video\/785042439?h=3f70aab841&amp;dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963\" width=\"950\" height=\"534\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-44\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-bloc